In fact we had 2 DHD's the DHD from Giza was taken by the Germans and then inturn taken by the Russians after WW2, and thats why they had one to power the second gate in Siberia (Watergate). However that DHD was destroyed in the ep 48 Hours. The other DHD was found in Antartica with the original Earth gate(solitudes) although that run out of power not long after it was found as it was one of the oldest DHD's possibly the first(Frozen).
To answer you question about the rock around the gate it probably did have one before it was buried.

Your a little inaccurate there Anubis.

The only recorded time the Goa'uld lost the "Giza gate" was when the people of Egypt rose up against Ra. He was either already on Abydos or he fled to Abydos. We saw frozen Jaffa next to the Antarctic gate, probably Jaffa sent back by Ra to Earth to see if the gate was open. With the Giza gate buried the Jaffa were re-directed to the freezing temperatures of Antarctica, now being the only place with an active gate on Earth. The Jaffa couldnt find a DHD to dial back to Ra and died from hypothermia. Ra assumed that it wasn't safe to return to Earth and thats the end of that.

I'm curious to know how Yu knew about the second gate however, as he mentionned it was to be removed along with the Giza gate when earth was attempting to join the protected planets treaty.
